\section{Goals of the CPAF}
The goals of the Cognitive Progression Analysis Framework are fairly large in number, and outlined in a dedicated document. However, for the purposes of this introduction, we will focus on the following key objectives:

\begin{itemize}
    \item To provide a unified framework for analyzing cognitive systems across different domains and scales.
    \item To explore the foundational elements and processes that underpin cognitive functions.
    \item To investigate the emergence of complex cognitive functions from basic elements and interactions.
    \item To examine the implications of advanced cognitive functions for understanding human and artificial intelligence.
    \item To do so in a fashion that is accessible to individuals at all levels of qualification or domain expertise, through leveraging it's own principles to explain itself.
    \item Given it's self referential nature, to adhere to a strong and consistent application of logical and mathematical rigour in it's explanations and derivations.
\end{itemize}

